<br>
1)  Just sell them back?  Seems you would lose a lot of money that way.<br>
2)  Buy ones you may need for some tradeskill item?<br>
3)  Give them to Casters for reagent cost re-imbursement?<br>
<br>
Please enlighten me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Kamdn Yards
Dwarven Cleric worshipper of Brell for 41 Seasons
Trusk
Human Monk of 24 Seasons</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unorpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norpin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand High Poobah</span><br>  Posts: 3694<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/26/02 7:08:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying Gems</span><hr size=1> 1. Just think of how after a while you have to start destroying gold.  The money you spend on gems is really money you would have destroyed anyways.<br>
<br>
2. If you are into tradeskills then yes, of course.<br>
<br>
3. That can work too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udryl00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dryl00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 275<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/26/02 8:34:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying Gems</span><hr size=1> Anyone of the three options you give are viable.  I have personally had to destroy many plat worth of bronze/silver/gold/&lt;wince&gt; even plat.  If I'm close enough to run to a merchant and buy gems, it beats destroying it.  What you lose on the single buy/sell cycle will be a fraction of what you destroy.  I've also been in some pick up groups where I was foregoing any share of loot because of weight but they were giving me the gems that dropped. <p><B><font size=2 color=blue >Dryl Fistmight</font></B>
<BR>
<font size=2 color=blue>46 Human Monk of Quellious</font>
<BR>
<font size=1 color=yellow>Proud member of</font>
<I><font size=2 color=yellow>Fatum ex Gladius</font></I>
<BR>
<I><font size=1 color=white>"when Prayer fails, a good fist does the trick"</font></I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tarrask>Tarrask</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/26/02 9:24:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying Gems</span><hr size=1> It doesn't have to be gems either - anything lightweight, fairly pricy and stackable works.  Gems are certainly the commonest things to fit this bill, but in certain places other items can work, for instance poisons from the vendor in LOIO. <p>Tarrask, 51st Swifttail of Saryrn
<BR>
<BR>
