<BR>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=231234/" target="_blank"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udaleb123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daleb123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 208<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/2/02 6:06:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Buying Gems</span><hr size=1> Also, you can obtain a stein with a large CHA bonus quite inexpensively now. Even if you just keep it in the bank and use it when selling them back, it will pay for itself in a month, and in the long run will save you a great deal of money. If you can carry it with you and use it on both ends of the transaction, it will pay for itself even faster. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urukirn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rukirn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/2/02 9:26:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> dots</span><hr size=1> I almost always buy a stack of peridots before I head out (210pp w/ max fac/cha) and often use them as currency either to get buffs (pay 2 maybe 3 dots for an aego), ports (usually do 3 dots) etc.  Most people either like them because someone they know can use them or like them because they can sell them to merch for 9+ pp.<br>
<br>
-Ruk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udarkcrayz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>darkcrayz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 407<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/7/02 7:57:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: dots</span><hr size=1> You buy the gems, so you can pay people with the gems, they turn around and sell them to a vendor for plat, and you dont weigh yourself with excess plat.<br>
<br>
raidawn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujunupeeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Junu Peeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/9/02 2:56:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: dots</span><hr size=1> If you have good enough faction (or sneak to indifferent) and have high enough CHA (104 will do in most cases) then you will only lose 9.3% on the purchase price of the gems you buy.<br>
<br>
Think of it as a conversion fee. Its not much when you are at the stage when you destroy gold and plat but have the chance to swap it for light weight gems. <p><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157667">Junu Peeth</a></b> on Mithaniel Marr<br>
